obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42982)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42982&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Provincial Small Cause Courts`
  line `Act, 1887.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States]; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42983)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42983&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal.] Rep. partly by the Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891), s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule and partly by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42984)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42984&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be construed to affect--`
  line
  line `(a) any proceedings before or after decree in any suit instituted before the commencement of this`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) The jurisdiction of a Magistrate under any law for the time being in force with respect`
  line `to debts or other claims of a civil nature, or of village-munsifs or village-panchayats, under the`
  line `provisions of the Madras Code, or of village-munsifs under the Dekkhan Agriculturists’ Relief`
  line `Act, 1879 (17 of 1879); or`
  line
  line `(c) any local law or any special law other than the Code of Civil Procedure^3`
  line
  line `(14 of 1882).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42985)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42985&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,`
  line `"Court of Small Causes" means a Court of Small Causes constituted under this Act, and includes`
  line `any person exercising jurisdiction under this Act in any such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42986)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Establishment of Courts of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42986&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government ^1*** may, by order`
  line `in writing, establish a Court of Small Causes at any place within the territories under its`
  line `administration beyond the local limits for the time being of the ordinary original civil jurisdiction`
  line `of a High Court of Judicature established in a Presidency-town.`
  line
  line `(2) The local limits of the jurisdiction of the Court of Small Causes shall be such as the State`
  line `Government may define, and the Court may be held at such place or places within those limits as the`
  line `State Government may appoint.^2`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." rep. by Act 4 of 1914. s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. For notifications issued under cl. (2) of s. 5, see different local R. and O.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42987)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Judge.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for section 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42987&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `b@^1[6. Judge.--When a Court of Small Causes has been established there shall be appointed, by order in`
  line `writing, a Judge of the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the State Government so direct, the same person shall be the Judge of more than one`
  line `such Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42988)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of times of sitting in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42988&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Judge who is the`
  line `Judge of two or more such Courts may, with the sanction of the District Court, fix the times at`
  line `which he will sit in each of the Courts of which he is Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) Notice of the times shall be published in such manner as the High Court from time to time directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42989)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Additional Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42989&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If the State Government so direct, there may be appointed, by`
  line `order in writing, Additional Judges of a Court of Small Causes or of two or more such Courts.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[An Additional] Judge shall discharge such of the functions of the Judge of the Court or`
  line `Courts as the Judge may assign to him, and in the discharge of those functions shall exercise the`
  line `same powers as the Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) The Judge may withdraw from ^2[an Additional] Judge any business pending before`
  line him.
  line
  line `(4) When the Judge is absent, the ^4[senior] Additional Judge may discharge all or any of the functions`
  line `of the Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for the sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1915, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "the Additional".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
