obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42991)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to require two Judges to si t as a bench.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42991&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The State Government, after`
  line `consultation with the High Court, may, by order in writing, direct that two Judges of Courts of`
  line `Small Causes or a Judge and an Additional Judge of a Court of Small Causes shall sit together`
  line `for the trial of such class or classes of suits or applications cognizable by a Court of Small`
  line `Causes as may be described in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
