obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43000)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Admission, return and rejection of plaints by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43000&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Judge of a`
  line `Court of Small Causes is absent, and an Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been`
  line `appointed, is also absent, the Registrar may admit a plaint, or return or reject a plaint for any`
  line `reason for which the Judge might return or reject it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judge may, of his own motion or on the application of a party, return or reject a`
  line `plaint which has been admitted by the Registrar, or admit a plaint which has been returned or`
  line `rejected by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a party applies for the return or rejection or the admission of a plaint`
  line `under this sub-section, and his application is not made at the first sitting of the Judge after the`
  line `day on which the Registrar admitted, or returned or rejected, the plaint, the Judge shall dismiss`
  line `the application unless the applicant satisfies him that there was sufficient caus e for not making`
  line `the application at that sitting.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43001)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Passing of decrees by Registrar on confession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43001&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, before the date appointed for`
  line `the hearing of a suit, the defendant or his agent duly authorised in that behalf appears before`
  line `the Registrar and admits the plaintiff's claim, the Registrar may, if the Judge is absent, and an`
  line `Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been appointed, is also absent, pass`
  line `against the defendant, upon the admission, a decree which shall have the same effect as a`
  line `decree passed by the Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a decree has been passed by the Registrar under sub-section (1), the Judge may`
  line `grant an application for review of judgment, and re -hear the suit, on the same conditions,`
  line `on the same grounds and in the same manner as if the decree had been passed by himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43002)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Execution of decrees by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43002&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Judge is absent, and an Additional`
  line `Judge has not been appointed or, having been appointed, is also absent, the Registrar may,`
  line `subject to any instructions which he may have received from the Judge or, with respect to decrees or orders made by an Additional Judge, from the Additional Judge, make any orders`
  line `in respect of applications for the execution of decrees and orders made by the Court of`
  line `which he is Registrar, or sent`
  line `to that Court for execution, which the Judge might make`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judge, in the case of any decree or order with respect to the execution of which the Registrar`
  line `has made an order under sub-section (1), or the Additional Judge, in the case of any such decree or order`
  line `which has been made by himself and with respect to which proceedings have not been taken by the Judge`
  line `under this sub-section, may, of his own motion, or on application made by a party within fifteen days`
  line `from the date of the order of the Registrar or of the execution of any process issued in pursuance of that`
  line `order, reverse or modify the order.`
  line
  line `(3) The period of fifteen days mentioned in sub-section (2) shall be computed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the ^1Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), as though the application of the party were an`
  line `application for review of judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43003)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Adjournment of cases by chief ministerial officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43003&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `When the Judge of a Court of`
  line `Small Causes is absent and an Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been`
  line `appointed, is also absent, the Registrar or other chief ministerial officer of the Court may`
  line `exercise from time to time the power which the Court possesses of adjourning the hearing of`
  line `any suit or other proceeding, and fix a day for the further hearing thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43004)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Return of plaints in suits involving questions of title .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43004&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `in the foregoing portion of this Act, when the right of a plaintiff and the relief claimed by him`
  line `in a Court of Small Causes depend upon the proof or disproof of a title to immovable property`
  line `or other title which such a Court cannot finally determine, the Court may at any stage of the`
  line `proceedings return the plaint to be presented to a Court having jurisdiction to determine the`
  line title.
  line
  line `(2) When a Court returns a plaint under sub-section (1), it shall comply with the`
  line `provisions of the second paragraph of ^1section 57 of the Code of Civil Procedure`
  line `(14 of 1882) and make such order with respect to costs as it deems just, and the Court`
  line `shall, for the purposes of the ^2Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), be deemed to have`
  line `been unable to entertain the suit by reason of a cause of a nature like to that of defect of`
  line jurisdiction.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order VII, rule 10.`
  line
  line `2. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43005)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appeal from certain orders of Courts of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43005&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where an order specified`
  line `in ^1[clause (ff) or clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 104 of the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908),] is made by a Court of Small Causes, an appeal therefrom shall lie to the`
  line `District Court ^2]on any ground on which an appeal from such order would lie under that`
  line section].
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1922, s. 5, for "section 588, clause ( 29), of the Code of Civil Procedure".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43006)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Revision of decrees and orders of Courts of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43006&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The High Court, for the`
  line `purpose of satisfying itself that a decree or order made in any case decided by a Court of`
  line `Small Causes was according to law, may call for the case and pass such order with respect`
  line `thereto as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 25 of Act IX of 1887.--In section 25 of principal Act, the`
  line `following proviso thereto shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"Provided that in relation to any case decided by a District Judge or Additional District`
  line `Judge exercising the jurisdiction of Judge of Small Causes, the power of revision under this`
  line `section shall vest in the High Court."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 37 of 1972, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (43007)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43007&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of the Second Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure.] Rep. by the`
  line `Presidency Small Cause Courts Law Amendment Act, 1888 (10 of 1888), s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (43008)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Finali ty of decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43008&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided by this Act, a decree or order`
  line `made under the foregoing provisions of this Act by a Court of Small Causes shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (43009)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Subordination of Courts of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43009&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Court of Small Causes shall be`
  line `subject to the administrative control of the District Court and to the superintendence of`
  line `the High Court, and shall--`
  line
  line `(a) keep such registers, books and accounts as the High Court from time to time`
  line `prescribes, and`
  line
  line `(b) comply with such requisitions as may be made by the District Court, the High`
  line `Court or the State Government for records, returns and statements in such form and`
  line `manner as the authority making the requisition directs.`
  line
  line `(2) The relation of the District Court to a Court of Small Causes, with respect to`
  line `administrative control, shall be the same as that of the District Court to a Civil Court of the`
  line `lowest grade competent to try an original suit of the value of five thousand rupees in that`
  line `portion of the territories administered by the State Gove rnment in which the Court of Small`
  line `Causes is established.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (43010)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Seal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43010&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `A Court of Small Causes shall use a seal of such form and dimensions as are`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (43011)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Abolit ion of Courts of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. For instance of a notification abolishing a Court of Small Causes (Broach), see Bombay Govt. Gazette, 1907, Pt. 1. p. 339.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43011&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by order in`
  line `writing, ^1abolish a Court of Small Causes.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (43012)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Saving of power to appoint Judge of Court of Small Causes to other office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43012&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall be construed to prevent ^1[the appointment of] a`
  line `person who is a Judge or Additional Judge of a Court of Small Causes to be also a Judge`
  line `of any other ^2Civil Court or to be a Magistrate of any class or to hold any other public`
  line office.
  line
  line `(2) When a Judge or Additional Judge is so appointed, the ministerial officers of his`
  line `Court shall, subject to any rules which the State Government may make in this behalf, be`
  line `deemed to be ministerial officers appointed to aid him in the disc harge of the duties of`
  line `the other office.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "`
  line `the L. G. from appointing".`
  line
  line `2. For instances of notifications issued under this power, see U. P. R. & 0.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (43019)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Application of Act to Courts invested with jurisdiction of Court of Small Causes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43019&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) So much of Chapters III and IV as relates to--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of the suits cognizable by Courts of Small Causes,`
  line
  line `(b) the exclusion of the jurisdiction of other Courts in those suits,`
  line
  line `(c) the practice and procedure of Courts of Small Causes,`
  line
  line `(d) appeal from certain orders of those Courts and revision of cases decided by`
  line `them, and`
  line
  line `(e) the finality of their decrees and orders subject to such appeal and revision as are provided by`
  line `this Act,`
  line
  line `applies to Courts invested by or under any enactment for .`
  line `the time being in force with the jurisdiction`
  line `of a Court of Small Causes so far as regards the exercise of that jurisdiction by those Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) with respect to Courts invested with the jurisdiction of a Court of Small`
  line `Causes applies to suits instituted or proceedings commenced in those Courts before the date on which`
  line `they were invested with that jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (43014)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Application of Act and Code to Court so invested as to two Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43014&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `A Court invested`
  line `with the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes with respect to the exercise of that jurisdiction, and`
  line `the same Court with respect to the exercise of its jurisdiction in suits of a civil nature which are not`
  line `cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, shall, for the purposes of this Act and the 1Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure (14 of 1882), be deemed to be different Courts.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (43015)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Modification of Code as so applied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. See now Order XXI, rule 6, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43015&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the last two foregoing`
  line sections,--
  line
  line `(a) when, in exercise of the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes, a Court invested with`
  line `that jurisdiction sends a decree for execution to itself as a Court having jurisdiction in suits`
  line `of a civil nature which are not cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, or`
  line
  line `(b) when a Court, in the exercise of its jurisdiction in suits of a civil nature which are not`
  line `cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, sends a decree for execution to itself as a Court invested with`
  line `the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes,`
  line
  line `the documents mentioned in ^1section 224 of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) shall not`
  line `be sent with the decree unless in any case the Court, by order in writing, requires them to be`
  line sent.
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (43016)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Continuance of proceedings of abolished Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43016&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Court of Small Causes, or`
  line `a Court invested with the Jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes, has from any cause ceased to`
  line `have jurisdiction with respect to any case, any proceeding in relation to the case, whether before or`
  line `after decree, which, if the Court had not ceased to have jurisdiction, might have been had therein,`
  line `may be had in the Court which, if the suit out of which the proceeding has arisen were about to be`
  line `instituted, would have jurisdiction to try the suit.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section applies to cases for which special provision is made in the 1Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure (14 of 1882) as extended to Courts of Small Causes or in any other enactment for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (43017)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43017&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of Indian Limitation Act.] Rep.by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908`
  line `(9 of 1908), s. 32 and the Third Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43018)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Publication of certain orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43018&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `All orders required by this Act to be made in writing by the`
  line `State Government shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `प्रान्‍तीय लघुवाद न्‍यायालय अधिनियम,1887`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/2312/3/H1887-9.pdf`
  sourceKind pdf
  fetchedAt `2026-05-10T10:11:53.489Z`
